	aside.notes
		ul
			li Bitcoin’s core innovation was the blockchain, a solution to distributed consensus in the presence of malicious nodes
			li Copy of ledger maintained by all nodes in a P2P network (decentralized ledger)
			li Transactions broadcast across network, unconfirmed until inclusion in block - indicates a “confirmation”
			li Mining involves finding the next block, which has a block reward and transaction fees, incentive
			li Average 10 minutes, Poisson process
			li Communication not instant, each can have a different view of blockchain. Rule is - longest chain wins
			li More confirmations means a transaction is harder to change

