	aside.notes
		ul
			li Only scratching the surface
			li Smart contracts are a promising use case for blockchain (applications include escrow, hedging contracts, notarizing documents, land registries, trade clearing/settlement, equity and corporate governance)
			li Lightning and Raiden networks use fast off-chain payment channels backed by on-chain settlement
			li ZCash uses advanced cryptography (zk-SNARKs) to support private transactions
			li Initiatives around enterprise adoption (private blockchains)
			li Governance models encoded within blockchain consensus rules (self-modifying)
			li Stellar - not a blockchain, instead based on trust lines
			li BigchainDB - adding immutable properties on top of existing DBs, this case Rethink
			li Crypto-economics
